What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Math 112 is difficult if you haven't taken calc before, but is survivable if you have a friend in it with you. Try to get Prof Lachowska because she's awesome.
Yes it's an easy QR credit and you should learn calculus at some point.

A class for pinning down your understanding of calculus; I took the class after taking and forgetting most of Calc AB in junior year of high school; the class was not difficult at all if you attend lectures and do the homework; tests are fair. Overall was satisfied with what I got out of this class.
Basic calculus class. Nothing special, but very doable.
A good intro calculus class to take. Anna Lachowska is a good professor. The exams were a lot harder than I was prepared for.
I took it as a prerequisite, it is no fun but also made interesting by some real-life applications, and my particular instructor was very kind.
Dude, if you want a relatively chill math course. Do it.

I would recommend it if it is a necessary requirement for a major of interest. The midterms/tests are hit or miss on difficulty level. Not everything can be explained in class, so seek help out of the classroom when uncertain about things.
